September 27, 1918,

182
00:08:06,987 --> 00:08:09,754
Neuse-argonne, France.

183
00:08:09,857 --> 00:08:13,091
Behind me, 1.3 million americans

184
00:08:13,193 --> 00:08:15,627
Are slowly advancing
through the forest.

185
00:08:15,729 --> 00:08:17,929
Doughboys,
we called them back then.

186
00:08:18,031 --> 00:08:20,165
The good news is there are only
a couple hundred thousand

187
00:08:20,267 --> 00:08:21,666
Germans over the hill.

188
00:08:21,768 --> 00:08:23,835
The americans
have the advantage,

189
00:08:23,937 --> 00:08:25,270
But for the fact

190
00:08:25,372 --> 00:08:28,273
That the germans have
in their possession a weapon

191
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:31,676
Unlike anything these kids
have ever seen,

192
00:08:31,778 --> 00:08:34,779
A weapon they're not
going to like.

193
00:08:39,286 --> 00:08:43,822
♪ ♪

194
00:08:43,924 --> 00:08:47,792
Introducing the maxim
machine gun,

195
00:08:47,895 --> 00:08:49,928
A weapon unlike any other.

196
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:56,101
Hiram maxim didn't create
the machine gun,

197
00:08:56,203 --> 00:09:00,238
He created the first
fully <i>automatic</i> machine gun.

198
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:07,245
♪ ♪

199
00:09:07,347 --> 00:09:10,215
Like his old mousetrap
that could catch multiple mice,

200
00:09:10,317 --> 00:09:12,651
Every time this thing fires off
a round,

201
00:09:12,753 --> 00:09:14,920
A new one
is automatically chambered.

202
00:09:15,022 --> 00:09:19,124
The result -- a complete
and total game changer.

203
00:09:19,226 --> 00:09:21,459
An internal component called
the breech block

204
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:23,628
Is pushed back
by the gun's recoil,

205
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:26,331
And the recoil ejects
the spent cartridge,

206
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:27,799
Making way for the next bullet,

207
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:31,303
Much like maxim's mouse trap
made way for the next mouse.

208
00:09:31,405 --> 00:09:32,637
But on balance,

209
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:37,709
Maxim's gun was slightly
more deadly than his mousetrap.

210
00:09:37,811 --> 00:09:41,212
It could fire
600 rounds per minute.

211
00:09:41,315 --> 00:09:43,682
There's the man himself,
hiram maxim,

212
00:09:43,784 --> 00:09:45,717
Crouched behind
what <i>the new york times</i>

213
00:09:45,786 --> 00:09:50,121
Would call "peace producing
and peace retaining terrors."

214
00:09:50,223 --> 00:09:53,024
The idea was that
such a powerful weapon

215
00:09:53,126 --> 00:09:56,494
Would push nations
to avoid conflict.

216
00:09:56,597 --> 00:09:59,264
Yeah, didn't really
work out that way.

217
00:10:01,168 --> 00:10:06,371
♪ ♪

218
00:10:06,473 --> 00:10:11,676
♪ ♪

219
00:10:18,485 --> 00:10:21,353
See what I mean?
Not good.

220
00:10:21,455 --> 00:10:23,788
Hiram maxim's little invention

221
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:26,091
Just wiped out
most of this squad

222
00:10:26,193 --> 00:10:27,559
In less than three seconds.

223
00:10:27,661 --> 00:10:30,395
This poor guy doesn't know
what to make of the situation.

224
00:10:30,497 --> 00:10:31,896
One minute he's walking
through the woods,

225
00:10:31,999 --> 00:10:33,465
The next minute
all his buddies are dead.

226
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:35,266
He doesn't know where
the shooting is coming from.

227
00:10:35,369 --> 00:10:37,736
He's in an obvious state
of shell shock,

228
00:10:37,838 --> 00:10:40,238
Has no idea what he's going to
do with that bayonet

229
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:41,573
On the end of his weapon.

230
00:10:41,675 --> 00:10:44,643
Meanwhile, the carnage
is unspeakable.

231
00:10:44,745 --> 00:10:46,845
This is a 30-caliber weapon.

232
00:10:46,947 --> 00:10:51,282
We're talking about firing
250 rounds every 30 seconds.

233
00:10:51,385 --> 00:10:53,918
This guy's been hit half
a dozen times.

234
00:10:54,021 --> 00:10:55,654
Of course, in 1918,

235
00:10:55,756 --> 00:10:57,522
There wouldn't have been much
left of him.

236
00:10:57,624 --> 00:10:58,990
We don't have that kind
of budget

237
00:10:59,092 --> 00:11:02,160
In the recreation department.

238
00:11:02,262 --> 00:11:04,596
During the reenactments,
we use blanks because,

239
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:07,699
Well, you know,
but out here on the gun range,

240
00:11:07,801 --> 00:11:10,301
The maxim gun is real,
the ammo is live,

241
00:11:10,404 --> 00:11:13,571
And the watermelons
and water coolers are doomed.

242
00:11:13,674 --> 00:11:20,345
♪ ♪

243
00:11:20,447 --> 00:11:27,118
♪ ♪

244
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:28,520
You just dumped
200 rounds.

245
00:11:28,622 --> 00:11:30,422
Geez.

246
00:11:30,524 --> 00:11:33,124
The situation is grim.

247
00:11:33,226 --> 00:11:35,393
The carnage is unspeakable,

248
00:11:35,495 --> 00:11:37,762
And the question is obvious.

249
00:11:37,864 --> 00:11:40,865
How are the americans
going to fight back

250
00:11:40,967 --> 00:11:42,834
Against a weapon like that?

251
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:49,307
